[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with causing Nether Wallop marquee crash injuries

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with causing injury by "wanton or furious" driving after a car was driven into a party marquee injuring eight people.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Peter Bialek, 66, of London Road, Salisbury, appeared at Basingstoke Magistrates' Court earlier on Saturday and was bailed until 19 April.
He also faces three counts of wounding with intent following the incident at Nether Wallop in October 2015.
Eight people were seriously hurt and six others suffered minor injuries.
